cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method to improve the disentanglement of latent factors in Variational AutoEncoders (VAEs) for image data. This is a problem that is commonly addressed in the machine learning subfields of computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves modifying the training process of VAEs, which is a technique commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses quantitative metrics to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which is a common practice in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
